# Trivy vulnerability exemptions — scoped to the 1code-api container image scan
# in .github/workflows/container-build.yml.
#
# FORMAT: `CVE-ID  # justification + expiry date`
# Review quarterly; remove entries as base-image rebuilds pull upstream fixes.
#
# CANONICAL REFERENCES:
# - docs/operations/roadmap.md "[Cleanup] Trivy exemption review" for expiry tracking
# - .github/workflows/container-build.yml line ~72 (Trivy step)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CVE-2026-28390  OpenSSL libssl3 CMS_decrypt NULL pointer dereference (DoS)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# First flagged: 2026-04-13 (v0.0.84 container build run 24326594244)
#
# Affected: openssl 3.0.18-1~deb12u2 (Debian bookworm stock) via
#          gcr.io/distroless/nodejs24-debian12 base image
# Fixed in: 3.0.19-1~deb12u2 (DSA-6201-1, bookworm-security)
# Source:   https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-28390
#
# Non-exploitability analysis for services/1code-api:
# - CVE affects CMS_decrypt() on attacker-controlled CMS EnvelopedData
#   (S/MIME / CMS-based protocols)
# - 1code-api does NOT process CMS or S/MIME data — it is a tRPC+Fastify HTTP
#   API for LiteLLM user/team/key provisioning (see services/1code-api/README.md)
# - libssl3 is transitively pulled in via Node.js TLS for outbound HTTPS to
#   Microsoft Graph + LiteLLM admin API; no CMS codepath reachable
# - FIPS modules are unaffected per upstream advisory
#
# Remediation plan:
# - Upstream distroless image rebuilds automatically when Debian security
#   updates land (typically within ~1 week of DSA publication)
# - Monitor gcr.io/distroless/nodejs24-debian12 digest; once the manifest
#   digest changes, bump services/1code-api/Dockerfile pin and remove this
#   exemption
# - Tracked: docs/operations/roadmap.md P2 "Refresh distroless base image pin"
CVE-2026-28390
